# Release packaging.
#
# `git archive` produces the core-kernel source drop.  The entries below
# are kept out of it: repo-internal metadata, and the separately-versioned
# `drivers` submodule (its contents live in github.com/tikuos/drivers).
# With drivers/ absent the Makefile's HAS_DRIVERS auto-detect resolves the
# driver table to the in-tree empty fallback
# (kernel/drivers/tiku_drv_empty_table.c), so the drop builds standalone.
#
# Build a release tarball with:
#   git archive --format=tar.gz --prefix=tikuos-0.05/ \
#       -o tikuos-0.05.tar.gz HEAD
#
# The larger sibling repositories (tikukits, TikuBench, examples, the
# host tooling) and all build artifacts are untracked here (.gitignore),
# so they are already excluded from the archive.

# Leading slash anchors to the repo root: `/drivers` excludes the
# top-level submodule only, NOT kernel/drivers (in-tree kernel code).
/.gitignore      export-ignore
/.gitattributes  export-ignore
/.gitmodules     export-ignore
/drivers         export-ignore
